item.title: By: Alex
item.dc:creator: Alex
item.description:
I've been trying to build a quadcopter on my own as a side project to my schooling and you're site has been an extremely reliable and useful source to me. Thank you. Although, I have encountered one thing that I am very curious about in your code. You continually use the phrases ">" and "<" with no reference to them anywhere in the code. Would you mind explaining what they are? Also, did you prefer using the mystery or the turnegy ESC, code wise, and if so, do you have to use the servo commands (milli vs deg) respectively? Thanks a ton!
~Alex
item.content:encoded:
I’ve been trying to build a quadcopter on my own as a side project to my schooling and you’re site has been an extremely reliable and useful source to me. Thank you. Although, I have encountered one thing that I am very curious about in your code. You continually use the phrases “>” and “<” with no reference to them anywhere in the code. Would you mind explaining what they are? Also, did you prefer using the mystery or the turnegy ESC, code wise, and if so, do you have to use the servo commands (milli vs deg) respectively?
Thanks a ton!

~Alex
